of life.<lb/>
It ought to be studied by the engineer who<lb/>
is employed in the construction of Canals; as<lb/>
certain <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">strata </hi> exceedingly hard are often with<lb/>
others very soft and easily cut through.-<lb/>
The drainer in order to make his operations<lb/>
successful ought to be minutely acquainted<lb/>
with the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">arrangement </hi> of the rocks in the<lb/>
