          Laertius
        </name>
            </rs> which<lb/>
I have thus translated.-<lb/>
He spoke of one eternal living mind<lb/>
That all this glorious universe designed<lb/>
And from compassion made it rise and shine<lb/>
In order and in harmony divine.-<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="56"
                xml:id="pb-56"
                facs="#i56"/>
            <lb/>
One of the most novel and the most remarkable<lb/>
of the doctrines of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
