               <name xml:id="tag83" type="place">
          Thrace
        </name>
            </rs> and that it left in its place<lb/>
a large and dark <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">coloured stone</hi> and that<lb/>
such <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">one</del> an event and that other events<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="58"
                xml:id="pb-58"
                facs="#i58"/>
            <lb/>
of the same kind would happen was<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">foretold</hi> by <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag84"
                ref="#person_605"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag84" type="person">
          Anaxagorus
        </name>
            </rs> -<lb/>
The few facts that we are in possession<lb/>
